UID:10004297-1775840400-1775854800@events.ackland.org
SUMMARY:2nd Friday ArtWalk: Documentary Photography
DESCRIPTION:Spend a spring evening learning more about documentary photography during this month’s 2nd Friday ArtWalk inspired by Bill Bamberger: Boys Will Be Men. \nArtist Bill Bamberger will offer tours of the exhibition alongside his faculty colleagues from the Duke Center for Documentary Studies while deputy director for curatorial affairs Peter Nisbet presents documentary photographs from the Ackland’s collection in special study room sessions. \nSpace is limited for the study room sessions. There are two opportunities to join: Session 1 from 6:00–6:45pm and Session 2 from 7:00–7:45pm. Please register below for your free ticket. \nThe event is free\, for all ages\, and all materials will be provided. The Museum will be open until 9 p.m. to see the exhibition and more. \n  \n  \n 
URL:https://events.ackland.org/event/2ndfridaydocumentaryphotographybwbm/
LOCATION:Ackland Art Museum\, 101 S. Columbia Street\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27514\, United States
CATEGORIES:2nd Friday ArtWalk,Special Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://events.ackland.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/5824c622-full1.jpg
END:VEVENT
